This project demonstrates how to deploy two NGINX-based applications â€” frontend and backend â€” in a Kubernetes cluster using Deployments, Services, and Ingress.
It also includes steps to access the apps through a single domain name using path-based routing.

ğŸ§± Components Used

Frontend Deployment: Runs 2 replicas of NGINX

Backend Deployment: Runs 1 replica of NGINX

Services: Expose each deployment internally using ClusterIP

Ingress: Routes external traffic to services using paths /frontend and /backend

